## Stochastic Trace Formula on Negatively Curved Manifolds

```math
\begin{aligned}
Z_{\Delta/2}(t) &= \mu(\Omega_t) = \mu(\Omega^0_t) + \sum_{\set{\text{closed geodesics }\gamma}} \mu(\Omega_t[\gamma]) \\

\mu(\Omega_t[\gamma]) &= e^{-\ell(\gamma)^2/2t}\mu(e^{-\ell(\gamma)x(t)}\Omega_t^0)\space\text{ by Cameron-Martin}\\

\frac{d\mu(e^{-\ell(\gamma)x(t)}
 \Omega^0_t)}{\sqrt{g}dx^1\dots dx^n}\vert_{\vec{x}+\gamma} &= \int_{\Reals^n/\ell(\gamma_0)\Z}\frac{e^{-\bra{(1-P_{\vec{x}+\gamma})\vec{x}\ket{\vec{x}}}/2t}}{(2 \pi t)^{n/2}}dx^1\dots dx^n\\

\implies\\

\mu(\Omega_t[\gamma]) &= \frac{e^{-\ell(\gamma)^2/2t}\ell(\gamma_0)e^{t\bar{K}(\gamma_0)/6}}{\sqrt{2\pi t\det{(I-P_\gamma)}}}(1 + O(t^2))
\end{aligned}
```

